This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on learning universal sentence representations. It also uses natural language processing techniques such as self-attention and pooling operations. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new autoencoder model for unsupervised learning. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it aims to learn universal sentence representations that can be used for various downstream tasks. 

It may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the proposed model uses attention mechanisms that are commonly used in image processing tasks. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it proposes a new neural network architecture for learning sentence representations.
